/-
PROBLEM
Generalized dedup correctness theorem with invariants

PROVIDED SOLUTION
By induction on cl, generalizing cr, G, n, set.

Case nil: cr must be .nil (by cases on wf). dedup_ .nil n set = .nil. .nil ≈ .nil by rfl.

Case assert_range: impossible, since wf has no assert_range constructor. Use cases/nomatch on wf.

Case lam kl ih: wf gives cr = .lam kr with ∀ el er, wf ({l:=el, r:=er}::G) (kl el) (kr er).
  dedup_ (.lam kr) n set = .lam (fun x => dedup_ (kr (n, x)) (n+1) set).
  Need .lam kl ≈ .lam (fun x => dedup_ (kr (n, x)) (n+1) set).
  By Circuit.lam_congr: for all x, kl x ≈ dedup_ (kr (n, x)) (n+1) set.
  Apply ih with G' = {l:=x, r:=(n,x)}::G, n' = n+1, set' = set.
