  eval (.is_zero el kl) = if el.eval = 0 then eval (kl 1) else eval (kl 0).
  eval (.is_zero (to_var er) ...) = if (to_var er).eval = 0 then eval (dedup_ (kr (n, 1)) (n+1) set) else eval (dedup_ (kr (n, 0)) (n+1) set).
  Since el.eval = (to_var er).eval, split on el.eval = 0:
  - If 0: need eval (kl 1) = eval (dedup_ (kr (n, 1)) (n+1) set). Apply ih with G' = {l:=1, r:=(n,1)}::G.
  - If ≠ 0: need eval (kl 0) = eval (dedup_ (kr (n, 0)) (n+1) set). Apply ih with G' = {l:=0, r:=(n,0)}::G.
